During a field mission to the mangrove forests of northern Mozambique, I introduced myself to the host communities as coming from Kenya.  Then I asked, “What do you know about Kenya?”
Majority of my audience had no clue about Kenya. Some even thought I was from Tanzania, Zimbabwe or Malawi. This is understandable considering that these countries border Mozambique. Having come across M-Pesa kiosks in the villages of Mozambique, I proceeded to ask, “Who knows about M-Pesa?”



