On this, all hands were up. I am sure there exists other mobile financial services in Mozambique, but when I saw how M-Pesa is impacting lives in rural Mozambique, I was proud to be a Kenyan.
My visit to Mozambique was organised through WWF-Country Office in Maputo.
WWF has an active marine programme in country and is currently implementing the Blue Forests project in Nampula and Zambezia provinces.





Climate change
Blue forests is a term used to denote coastal vegetated wetlands such as mangrove forests and seagrass beds. In addition to providing habitats for fish, blue forests capture and stores huge stocks of carbon in both above and below ground components. When degraded, they not only halt storing carbon but more importantly they release the stored carbon back to the atmosphere causing climate change. It is for these reasons that many countries are including blue forests in their national development and climate change agenda.
Due to language barriers, a local translator, Mr Lourenco Ernesto Papissone, aka Cassava, was assigned to me. Cassava and I traversed coastal villages in Angoche and Mona districts collecting data on mangrove forests, threats facing them, and opportunities for their restoration and management within Premerias and Secundas Environment Protected Area; abbreviated as PSEPA.



