So far, Mikoko Pamoja has provided educational materials to 900 school children, improved water access for 5,000 community members and ensured that the 615ha of mangroves in Gazi bay are restored and protected. 
In 2017, Mikoko Pamoja won the coveted United Nations Equator Prize.
Activities of Mikoko Pamoja have so far been replicated in Vanga bay, in Kenya, as well as in Madagascar. It is on this basis that we ventured to replicate a similar carbon offset facility for the benefit of climate, community and biodiversity in PSEPA.
Journey to Mozambique
Regulations required that a Covid-19 test be taken 72 hours prior to travelling to Mozambique. For this, I proceeded to Mombasa Hospital for the test on December 11, 2020 that turned out negative.  A similar test was repeated in Mozambique on December 22 to allow me travel back home. The two Covid-19 tests cost an equivalent of Sh18,000.
A Kenyan national visiting Mozambique for less than three months does not require a visa. I took advantage of this provision and headed to the airport immediately I received my Covid results. Five hours later, I am in Nampula via Lilongwe, Malawi, on Kenya Airways fight KQ 576. A return journey direct to Nairobi takes less than three hours.



